.za 1.5
.ue 1
                                                                       $.#$
                                                        <1858>* <Juli (?)>*

My dear Marie

.ue 2
                                                                       $.#$
Forts.: <1858>* <Juli (?)>*
You are the plurality well, as you write, of which I am very glad. But this
plurality is a singularity: I mean it is a word very oddly used. We are for
the most part well or Most of us etc will do. Mrs Mgl is I think well - Mrs
Hoch weak. She will be glad to stay some days with us at Calicut when they
return to Mang in Oct. then you may hear stories about your first time at
Gundeld which will have long been forgotten by your memory.

Lieut Hay here (of Gomp's Regt) knows already of God's doings at Mang. and
is somewhat startled and coming near. It seems that Taylor the Ind. Navy
Captain is very well known every where, also up here, and as a clever man
his being converted makes some noise. May it do so to some purpose
.fo -
                                 Your Papa


